## 🧭 System Context

The **Hazards Transformation Layer** is the **QA and harmonization engine** for all incoming datasets.  
It standardizes coordinate reference systems, spatial resolutions, temporal coverage, and CF metadata before datasets proceed to the **Validation**, **AI**, and **Graph Integration** stages.

**Responsibilities**
- Reproject datasets to **EPSG:4326**.  
- Enforce **CF metadata conventions** (variable units, global attributes).  
- Convert imagery to **COG/PMTiles** for performance and offline use.  
- Validate CRS/FAIR+CARE integrity and register lineage to the **Governance Ledger**.

> *“Transformation is geometry learning its ethical coordinates.”*

---

## 🗂️ Directory Layout

```text
data/work/tmp/hazards/transforms/
├── flood_extents_cf/               # Harmonized flood COGs (GeoTIFF/CF)
├── tornado_tracks_cf/              # Tornado path normalization output
├── wildfire_perimeters_cf/         # Fire polygon reprojection & resampling
├── usdm_drought_cf/                # Drought index harmonization
├── cf_fix_logs.json                # CF compliance fix history
├── reprojection_trace.log          # CRS reprojection history
├── tiling_resample.log             # Resampling, pyramiding, COG generation trace
├── harmonization_summary.json      # Variable/unit harmonization summary
├── spatial_resolution_audit.csv    # Resolution audit across datasets
├── transform_checksums.json        # SHA-256 verification for transformed assets
├── transform_manifest.json         # Input→Output lineage manifest
└── README.md
```

---

## ⚙️ Make Targets (Transformation Ops)

```text
make hazards-transform-run         # Perform CF harmonization and reprojection
make hazards-transform-verify      # Validate CRS, metadata, checksum, FAIR+CARE
make hazards-transform-checksum    # Generate and verify SHA-256 hashes
make hazards-transform-ledger      # Register transformation manifest to Governance Ledger
```

